// f128 differential oracle: DEFERRED to sq-3x7dl.14.2.
// Reason: Rust `f128` is nightly-only (unstable) and no stable soft-float
// binding with verified IEEE 754 quad-precision conformance is available
// without heavy external deps (MPFR C bindings, etc.).  The sparq_ieee754
// f128 type uses a `u128`/Field 'wide kernel' that is tested by the Noir
// unit tests in src/lib.nr; a proper differential oracle will be added when
// a stable Rust f128 type or a suitable pure-Rust soft-float crate is available.

